t: Luke 19
And*p Jesus entered and passed through Jericho.
And,*p behold, there was a man named Zacchaeus, which was the chief among the publicans, and he was rich.
And*p he sought to see Jesus who he was; and could not for the press, because he was little of stature.
And*p he ran before, and climbed up into a sycomore tree to see him: for he was to pass that way.
And*p when Jesus came to the place, he looked up, and saw him, and said unto him, Zacchaeus,*r make*r haste,*r and*r come*r down;*r for*r to*r day*r I*r must*r abide*r at*r thy*r house.*r
And*p he made haste, and came down, and received him joyfully.
And*p when they saw it, they all murmured, saying, That he was gone to be guest with a man that is a sinner.
And*p Zacchaeus stood, and said unto the Lord; Behold, Lord, the half of my goods I give to the poor; and if I have taken any thing from any man by false accusation, I restore him fourfold.
And*p Jesus said unto him, This*r day*r is*r salvation*r come*r to*r this*r house,*r forsomuch*r as*r he*r also*r is*r a*r son*r of*r Abraham.*r
For*rp the*r Son*r of*r man*r is*r come*r to*r seek*r and*r to*r save*r that*r which*r was*r lost.*r
And*p as they heard these things, he added and spake a parable, because he was nigh to Jerusalem, and because they thought that the kingdom of God should immediately appear.
He*p said therefore, A*r certain*r nobleman*r went*r into*r a*r far*r country*r to*r receive*r for*r himself*r a*r kingdom,*r and*r to*r return.*r
And*rp he*r called*r his*r ten*r servants,*r and*r delivered*r them*r ten*r pounds,*r and*r said*r unto*r them,*r Occupy*r till*r I*r come.*r
But*rp his*r citizens*r hated*r him,*r and*r sent*r a*r message*r after*r him,*r saying,*r We*r will*r not*r have*r this*r man*r to*r reign*r over*r us.*r

And*rp it*r came*r to*r pass,*r that*r when*r he*r was*r returned,*r having*r received*r the*r kingdom,*r then*r he*r commanded*r these*r servants*r to*r be*r called*r unto*r him,*r to*r whom*r he*r had*r given*r the*r money,*r that*r he*r might*r know*r how*r much*r every*r man*r had*r gained*r by*r trading.*r
Then*rp came*r the*r first,*r saying,*r Lord,*r thy*r pound*r hath*r gained*r ten*r pounds.*r
And*rp he*r said*r unto*r him,*r Well,*r thou*r good*r servant:*r because*r thou*r hast*r been*r faithful*r in*r a*r very*r little,*r have*r thou*r authority*r over*r ten*r cities.*r
And*rp the*r second*r came,*r saying,*r Lord,*r thy*r pound*r hath*r gained*r five*r pounds.*r
And*rp he*r said*r likewise*r to*r him,*r Be*r thou*r also*r over*r five*r cities.*r
And*rp another*r came,*r saying,*r Lord,*r behold,*r here*r is*r thy*r pound,*r which*r I*r have*r kept*r laid*r up*r in*r a*r napkin:*r
For*rp I*r feared*r thee,*r because*r thou*r art*r an*r austere*r man:*r thou*r takest*r up*r that*r thou*r layedst*r not*r down,*r and*r reapest*r that*r thou*r didst*r not*r sow.*r

And*rp he*r saith*r unto*r him,*r Out*r of*r thine*r own*r mouth*r will*r I*r judge*r thee,*r thou*r wicked*r servant.*r Thou*r knewest*r that*r I*r was*r an*r austere*r man,*r taking*r up*r that*r I*r laid*r not*r down,*r and*r reaping*r that*r I*r did*r not*r sow:*r
Wherefore*rp then*r gavest*r not*r thou*r my*r money*r into*r the*r bank,*r that*r at*r my*r coming*r I*r might*r have*r required*r mine*r own*r with*r usury?*r

(And*rp they*r said*r unto*r him,*r Lord,*r he*r hath*r ten*r pounds.)*r

For*rp I*r say*r unto*r you,*r That*r unto*r every*r one*r which*r hath*r shall*r be*r given;*r and*r from*r him*r that*r hath*r not,*r even*r that*r he*r hath*r shall*r be*r taken*r away*r from*r him.*r

And*p when he had thus spoken, he went before, ascending up to Jerusalem.
And*p it came to pass, when he was come nigh to Bethphage and Bethany, at the mount called the mount of Olives, he sent two of his disciples,

Saying,*p Go*r ye*r into*r the*r village*r over*r against*r you;*r in*r the*r which*r at*r your*r entering*r ye*r shall*r find*r a*r colt*r tied,*r whereon*r yet*r never*r man*r sat:*r loose*r him,*r and*r bring*r him*r hither.*r
And*rp if*r any*r man*r ask*r you,*r Why*r do*r ye*r loose*r him?*r thus*r shall*r ye*r say*r unto*r him,*r Because*r the*r Lord*r hath*r need*r of*r him.*r
And*p they that were sent went their way, and found even as he had said unto them.
And*p as they were loosing the colt, the owners thereof said unto them, Why loose ye the colt?
And*p they said, The Lord hath need of him.
And*p they brought him to Jesus: and they cast their garments upon the colt, and they set Jesus thereon.
And*p as he went, they spread their clothes in the way.

And*p when he was come nigh, even now at the descent of the mount of Olives, the whole multitude of the disciples began to rejoice and praise God with a loud voice for all the mighty works that they had seen;
Saying,*p Blessed be the King that cometh in the name of the Lord: peace in heaven, and glory in the highest.
And*p some of the Pharisees from among the multitude said unto him, Master, rebuke thy disciples.
And*p he answered and said unto them, I*r tell*r you*r that,*r if*r these*r should*r hold*r their*r peace,*r the*r stones*r would*r immediately*r cry*r out.*r
And*p when he was come near, he beheld the city, and wept over it,
Saying,*p If*r thou*r hadst*r known,*r even*r thou,*r at*r least*r in*r this*r thy*r day,*r the*r things*r which*r belong*r unto*r thy*r peace!*r but*r now*r they*r are*r hid*r from*r thine*r eyes.*r
For*rp the*r days*r shall*r come*r upon*r thee,*r that*r thine*r enemies*r shall*r cast*r a*r trench*r about*r thee,*r and*r compass*r thee*r round,*r and*r keep*r thee*r in*r on*r every*r side,*r

And*rp shall*r lay*r thee*r even*r with*r the*r ground,*r and*r thy*r children*r within*r thee;*r and*r they*r shall*r not*r leave*r in*r thee*r one*r stone*r upon*r another;*r because*r thou*r knewest*r not*r the*r time*r of*r thy*r visitation.*r
And*p he went into the temple, and began to cast out them that sold therein, and them that bought;
Saying*p unto them, It*r is*r written,*r My*r house*r is*r the*r house*r of*r prayer:*r but*r ye*r have*r made*r it*r a*r den*r of*r thieves.*r
And*p he taught daily in the temple. But the chief priests and the scribes and the chief of the people sought to destroy him,
And*p could not find what they might do: for all the people were very attentive to hear him.
